element.name: Family in need validation & submission approval
3.1. Location
element.documentation: Location of the user

element.name: 3.2. Device
element.documentation: Device through which the user connects to the platform

element.name: 1.2. Messaging
element.documentation: Direct messaging between users. Include: * Text messages * Email * Voice Chat * Video Char * Reactions

element.name: 1.3. Collaboration
element.documentation: Ability of a user to collaborate with other user or users, by interact with the contents or messaging shared. Include the rules that govern the interactions

element.name: 1.4. Connection
element.documentation: Ability of a user to find and connect with other users, bases on their profile and defined rules.

element.name: 1.1. Sharing
element.documentation: Asset sharing between users, based on profile and relation with the author of the content.

element.name: 4.4. Redemption Prizes
element.documentation: Management of prices and its associated points

element.name: 4.2. Scoring rules
element.documentation: Rules by a user can obtain points

element.name: 4.1. Score
element.documentation: Scoring management for each user, including the history of movements.

element.name: 4.3. Redemption Rules
element.documentation: Rules by a user can redem points for prices, products or services.

element.name: 6.1. Marketplace
element.documentation: Functions allowing the creation. maintenance and deletion of market place related to the users of the platforms, based on the profile and business rules

element.name: 6.2. Product
element.documentation: These functions allows the management of the product Catalog, aiming the creation, configuration (based on redemption rules), modification and elimination of products that can be changed by points.

element.name: 7.4. Information Management
element.documentation: Governance and caring of all the information produced by the company, including transactional information, documents, internal wikis and public content.

element.name: 7.5. Finance & Treasury
element.documentation: Finance management. Caring of the accounting and the health of the company in financial ways.

element.name: 7.7. Enterprise Wide IT
element.documentation: Process, methods and tools that rule the IT proces and lifecycle, ensuring quality and speed on value delivery

element.name: 7.8. Risk & Fraud Management
element.documentation: Risk control and lifecycle management

element.name: 7.1. Investments
element.documentation: Investment Management to ensure the ongoing and future business

element.name: 7.6. Integration Management
element.documentation: In a complex architecture, it is necessary to manage and govern the integration components, including: - APIs governance - Sync integration - Async integrations

element.name: 7.3. Regulatory Compliance
element.documentation: Compliance management, controlling the appliance of procedures and controls to ensure the conformance to local, regional and international regulations

element.name: 7.2. Human Resources
element.documentation: Managing the employee lifecycle and experience, including: - onboarding - offboarding - upskilling - recruiting

element.name: 5.3. Analytics
element.documentation: Analytics capabilities, including * Engagement * Scoring * Recommendations * Trends

element.name: 5.2. Widgets
element.documentation: Widgets to create custom pages or application using the information of the platform (e.g. merchant commerce)

element.name: 5.5. Authentication & Authorization
element.documentation: Authentication and authorization capabilities. Including the ability to validate the user credentials with a third party (e.g. oauth identity provider)

element.name: 5.4. Notifications
element.documentation: Notification of the activity in the platform to a user, per instance via mobile or browser.

element.name: 5.7. Privacy and Security
element.documentation: Privacy and security management, including GDPR

element.name: 5.6. Content
element.documentation: Content management

element.name: 5.1. APIs
element.documentation: Application Program Interfaces that aim another developers to interact with the platform, converting the social network in a platform providing value to a broader ecosystem..

element.name: 2.3. Social Graph
element.documentation: Management of the social graph, showing the relationship of a user with the universe of users in the platform. Includes: * Contacts * Groups * Brands * Access control

element.name: 2.4. Profile
element.documentation: Profile management of the user in the social network, including: * Profile page * Profile Data * Presence * Location * Skills / habilities

element.name: 2.2. Addressing
element.documentation: Addressing characteristics of the users, including: * snail mail address * email address * Social URIs

element.name: 2.1. Identity
element.documentation: Identity of each users, including: * Given and family name (for persons) * Company name (for organizations) * User name * Identity information (ID number, taxes ID, etc)

element.name: CONS.04. The officer location feature must be implemented in a way that ensure the officer confidence on its privacy, non disclosure and safety
CONS.06. [Assumption] Define a solution that evolve with a team
element.documentation: Currently ther is no IT team. Define a solution that can be implemented in a simple way, with a simple team first, and evolve later.

element.name: CONS.08. Solution should be launched on september 11, 2023
CONS.03. The solution should be limited to USA cities (by Zip Codes)
CONS.01. The cost should be as little as possible
element.documentation: HeyBlue is a non-profit company. The use of resources should be wisely defined. Choose the cheapest alternative if it is possible.

element.name: CONS.02. Application should be mobile and web
CONS.05. [Assumption] There is no restriction about technology
AC.STA.01. [Assumption] Uptime 99.95% from monday to friday 9AM to 10PM
AC.SEC.02. End User AAA
element.documentation: The users of the application (Police officiers, civilians, charity and business) must be properly authenticated to use the applications, and can only access the functionality and information that is allowed to their profile.

element.name: AC.CON.03. [HARD] Officers location must automatically shut off after 15 minutes
AC.SEC.04. Community members find the officers that are willing to connect, officers cannot find the community members
AC.PER.02. [Assumption] Changes in the civilian and police officer score should happen in less than 2 minutes before action (connection, redeption or donation)
AC.CON.02. A connection can only happen if the community member and the police officer are within a 10 ft distance from each other
AC.SEC.05 [Assumption] User profile should be validated for each user (civilian, police officer, family in needs, business, charity)
AC.CON.01. Users can only have one connection per officer per 24 hours period.
AC.SCA.01. [Assumption] Start with little use rate (Friends and Family) and scalate the solution as usage rate increase
AC.PER.01. [Assumption] Connection between police officer and civilians should be stablished in less than 5 seconds from the civilian intention
AC.MOD.01. [Assumption] Integrate with another social media in less than two agile iterations
AC.STA.02. [Assumption] Uptime 99,95% from saturday to sunday from 7AM to 11:59PM
AC.USA.03. [Assumption] Omnichannel experience
element.documentation: The solution must ensure an omnichannel experience, meaning that the information showne in a given channel (e.g. mobile) should be the same that other channels at the same time (e.g. web).

element.name: AC.SEC.03. Device linking
element.documentation: Users must link an email address to a particular phone or device. No user must be able to register multiple devices linked to an email address.

element.name: AC.SEC.01. Secure information
element.documentation: The application must protect user data, considering what data is stored and what data is transient
